important; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">When brewing iced coffee on the Aeropress, we tend to use a&nbsp;**1:16 ratio**&nbsp;of coffee to water and ice.</p><p style="text-align: inherit!important; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br></p><p style="text-align: inherit!important; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">For this recipe, we'll use 16g of coffee, 128g &nbsp;of water and 128g of ice.</p><p style="text-align: inherit!important; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br></p><p style="text-align: inherit!important; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">A note about your coffee: beans that are naturally processed tend to taste delicious as iced coffees - the natural process of the coffee really sings when made this way!</p><p style="text-align: inherit!important; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br></p><p style="text-align: inherit!important; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">What youâ€™ll need</p><p style="text-align: inherit!important; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">- &nbsp;Aeropress or Aeropress Go</p><p style="text-align: inherit!important; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">- Aeropress filter papers</p><p style="text-align: inherit!important; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">- A pitcher with at least 500ml capacity</p><p style="text-align: inherit!important; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">- Scales</p><p style="text-align: inherit!important; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br></p></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1684406972230" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1684406972230" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/9c1c8b98-c372-4312-b322-18b7d5e396b6/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Japanese%20Iced%20Coffee_%20Aeropress%20and%20Pour%20Over%20%E2%80%94%20Handsome%20Wade.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" width="1024" height="683" natural-width="1024" natural-height="683"></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1684407109429" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1684407109429"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><br></span></p><p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Method</span></p><p><br></p><p>1. Grind your coffee a bit finer than you would for a normal brew.</p><p><br></p><p>2. Heat water to 92C.</p><p><br></p><p>3. Preheat your Aeropress and rinse the filter. Do&nbsp;**not**&nbsp;preheat your pitcher.</p><p><br></p><p>4. Put 128g of ice in the pitcher.</p><p><br></p><p>5. Start your brew by adding 128g of water into the brewing chamber and give it a good stir.</p><p><br></p><p>6. After 1 minute, plunge your Aeropress into your pitcher.</p><p><br></p><p>7. By the end of your brew, all the ice in your pitcher should have melted. If it is not all melted, you can decrease the amount of ice in future brews.</p><p><br></p><p>8. Serve in a cool glass with ice. Enjoy!</p><p><br></p></div></div><!--gfsplit--><script>window.__gemStoreData = {};window.__gemStoreData.gemKeyValid = {};window.__gemStoreData.gemKeyValid.bestWayAddToCart = 1;</script></div><div id="divContentBk"></div><!--End_Gem_Page_Main_Editor-->
